element.name: Metadata Management
element.documentation: Capabilities applicable to full “Metadata Management” scope, such as storage, stewardship, reporting, and administration of metadata.

element.name: Business Intelligence & Analytics
element.documentation: Capabilities applicable to the full scope of BI & Analytics.

element.name: Business Support
element.documentation: Human resources, finance, and procurement.

element.name: Core business primary activities supporting value chain
element.documentation: Supporting the value chain of the Business Model

element.name: Engagement
element.documentation: CRM (supporting sales and services, including lead management).

element.name: Integration & Interoperability
element.documentation: BI & Analytics gathers and distributes data through the integration platforms (ESB, ETL, API).

element.name: Master Data Management
element.documentation: MDM

element.name: External partner capabilities
element.documentation: Data exposed on the Internet through the Representational State Transfer (REST) API.

element.name: External data provider capabilities
element.documentation: Data exposed through a website URL on the Internet.

element.name: Core business primary activities supporting value chain
element.documentation: Supporting the value chain of the Business Model

element.name: Engagement
element.documentation: Includes the key capabilities that are used to interact with the customer, business users and partners. It covers the digital, service center, distribution and partners channels (B2B2C). This category also includes the CRM marketing, servicing and sales as key enablers for this layer

element.name: Prospect & Customer Digital Access
element.documentation: (Web, Appli, IoT...)

element.name: Marketing
element.documentation: Market Study, Segmentation, Campaign

element.name: Infrastructure
element.documentation: Includes cloud

element.name: Master Data Management
element.documentation: MDM

element.name: Integration & Interoperability
element.documentation: Data Integration & Interoperability (DII) describes processes related to the movement and consolidation of data within and between data stores, applications and organizations. Integration consolidates data into consistent forms, either physical or virtual. Data interoperability is the ability for multiple systems to communicate Tools that support this capability are usually : ESB, ETL, API

element.name: Business metadata storage
element.documentation: Storage of business metadata: non-technical information about data. Capabilities applicable to full “Business Metadata Storage” scope.

element.name: Data glossary
element.documentation: Storage of business metadata, such as business name, definition. Uniqueness should be respected in the data glossary.

element.name: Data quality
element.documentation: Storage of business data quality rules and measurement.

element.name: Data usage
element.documentation: Storage of data usage activities, including processing identification of personal data.

element.name: Reference data
element.documentation: Storage of reference data (hierarchies) needed for reporting

element.name: Data stewardship
element.documentation: Storage of information, such as the stakeholders in charge of data management.

element.name: Data classification
element.documentation: Storage of data classification: privacy, security, valuable assets, etc..

element.name: Repository administration
element.documentation: Administration of the Metadata Management (workflow, authorization, etc.).

element.name: Technical metadata storage
element.documentation: Storage of technical metadata: information about the technical details of the data (schema, links, access, etc.).

element.name: Data dictionaries
element.documentation: Storage of data dictionaries (databases, tables, columns).

element.name: Data access
element.documentation: Storage of data access permissions.

element.name: Metadata reporting
element.documentation: Generation of report on Enterprise Metadata repository.

element.name: Metadata stewardship
element.documentation: Addition of business metadata related to data.

element.name: Administration
element.documentation: Administration tasks required to support BI & Analytics capabilities such as access management, scheduling data processing, etc. Requirements listed here apply to the full scope.

element.name: Resources management
element.documentation: Resources management of BI & Analytics.

element.name: Access management
element.documentation: Identity and access management, mainly including authentication and authorization services for users and administrators.

element.name: Scheduling
element.documentation: Job scheduler administration.

element.name: Service recovery
element.documentation: Recovery of the service after a disaster.

element.name: Manage Laboratory & Production environment
element.documentation: Management of different environments: production, test, development.

element.name: Data processing
element.documentation: Services that allow data transformation including basic preparations or more advanced features calculations leveraging statistics or data science. Requirements listed here apply to the full scope.

element.name: Batch processing
element.documentation: Daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly data transfers performed by batch.

element.name: Near realtime processing
element.documentation: Low-latency data processing – less than 24 hours/day (includes micro batch and near-real time, with minute or second latency).

element.name: Business transformation
element.documentation: Business processing (filtering, aggregation, joining, and de-duplication).

element.name: Technical preparation
element.documentation: Business-agnostic technical processing common to all use-cases (i.e., type format, cleansing, integration).

element.name: Masking
element.documentation: Anonymizing or pseudonymizing BI & Analytics data.

element.name: Quality profiling
element.documentation: Profiling of data quality through statistical techniques. - Inconsistent value - Duplicate records - Missing values - Invalid data - Outliers

element.name: Statistical computing
element.documentation: Data science and statistical processing (classification, clustering of data using statistics, data science modeling, including machine learning).

element.name: Metadata infering
element.documentation: Process of deducing properties of data-such as type, classification, metadata, etc. through the analysis of the data itself.

element.name: Deletion
element.documentation: Deletion of data from BI & Analytics (i.e., GDPR).

element.name: Change Data Capture
element.documentation: Ingestion or distribution of change data capture flows.

element.name: Monitoring
element.documentation: Monitoring services for infrastructure, network, and application to guarantee the service level agreed.

element.name: Business usage monitoring
element.documentation: Monitoring of the business services of the platform (supervise data science model drifting, etc.).

element.name: Technical monitoring
element.documentation: Monitoring of the network layer and infrastructure layer.

element.name: Security monitoring
element.documentation: Monitoring of the security layer.

element.name: Lineage & audit
element.documentation: Capture of the data lifecycle, including the data origin and where it moves over time

element.name: Data & application monitoring
element.documentation: Monitoring of the data (e.g., quality) and application layer (e.g., availability of services).

element.name: Data engineering and data science development
element.documentation: Capabilities applicable to the developer’s workstation.

element.name: Data wrangling & data discovery tools
element.documentation: Data preparation tooling for the data engineer or data scientist

element.name: Development in Integrated Environment (IDE)
element.documentation: Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for the data engineer or data scientist.

element.name: Interactive notebook-like development
element.documentation: Notebook environment (for data analytics in early exploration phase, algorithm comparison) for data scientists, data engineers, and graphical presentation of data.

element.name: Statistic&machine learning tools
element.documentation: Statistic and machine learning tools for data scientists and data engineers.

element.name: Integration and deployment
element.documentation: Continuous delivery chain, including versioning, deployment, packaging, etc.

element.name: Source code management
element.documentation: Versioning of development code (trunk) and release (branch) for developers or data scientists.

element.name: Deployment
element.documentation: Deploy a package – new software release – on a given environment (development, integration, pre-production, production).

element.name: Build management
element.documentation: Prepare the package to be deployed: run the test and generate binaries.

element.name: Testing
element.documentation: Execution of tests on the new code release (non-regression).

element.name: Information reporting & dashboarding
element.documentation: Support reporting and dashboarding activities using data stored in BI & Analytics (e.g., Microsoft® BI or SAP® BI).

element.name: Information servicing
element.documentation: Storage of information data in a format adapted to queries (cube, in memory, view, etc.).

element.name: Formatted online reporting
element.documentation: Ready-to-use reports and charts that can be refreshed interactively to use data with no specific data management skills.

element.name: Report diffusion scheduling
element.documentation: Ready-to-use static reports, charts generated periodically, usually paginated and in a printable format

element.name: Self service reporting
element.documentation: Build reports and refresh them with data. Ability for a business user – with no SQL skill, and a drag-and-drop UI – to create a report from available information and share it with other users.

element.name: Basic data tables manipulation & analysis
element.documentation: Example : Information analysis in Office Excel

element.name: Data ingestion & distribution
element.documentation: Services that allow integration and BI & Analytics in the full landscape including batch, streaming, interfaces, etc. Requirements listed here apply to the full scope.

element.name: Metadata Exchange
element.documentation: Metadata ingestion and distribution in parallel from data.

element.name: Batch Exchange
element.documentation: Scheduled asynchronous distribution of files

element.name: Query Execution
element.documentation: Synchronous Java® Database Connectivity (JDBC) or Open Database Connectivity (ODBC) database connection.

element.name: Manual upload or download
element.documentation: Integration of a file provided by an end user or download of a set of data.

element.name: Data interface
element.documentation: Web service integration, APIs, etc.

element.name: Streaming
element.documentation: Streaming through a messaging system that transports and secures data flow back pressure.

element.name: External device connection
element.documentation: Integration with an external device connection.

element.name: In-transit encryption
element.documentation: Protection of data transport through encryption of the data in motion (transit) on the network.

element.name: Interface Management
element.documentation: Capabilities applicable to full “Interface Management” scope to provide a central point to monitor and configure interfaces in a self-service mode for entities.

element.name: Decision support analysis & visualization
element.documentation: Support data discovery and visualization using data stored in BI & Analytics (e.g., TIBCO Spotfire®, Tableau®).

element.name: Dynamic data preparation
element.documentation: Data dynamic preparation, with no persistence, to allow statistical processing.

element.name: Visual data discovery
element.documentation: Dynamic drill down to navigate the data and find the right chart, graphic, etc.

element.name: Statistical analysis
element.documentation: Apply dynamic statistical “on-the-shelf” models to information available online.

element.name: Data access for data management use
element.documentation: Navigation through data from the Datalake's storage or the Enterprise Metadata repository's storage.

element.name: Data visualization
element.documentation: Navigation through data from the Datalake's storage or the Enterprise Metadata repository's storage.

element.name: Metadata exploration
element.documentation: Ability to explore the metadata of BI & Analytics. - Storage of operational Metadata generated from data like lineage, access log, quality. - Storage of business information related to data like glossary, classification. - Storage of technical information related to data such as schema description.

element.name: SQL data access
element.documentation: Ability to perform Structured Query Language (SQL) queries directly on BI & Analytics storage.

element.name: Search data access
element.documentation: Ability to search for data through a search engine directly on BI & Analytics storage.

element.name: Data storage
element.documentation: Services that allow persistent storage of structured or unstructured data. Requirements listed here apply to the full scope.

element.name: Stored data encryption
element.documentation: Protection of data within a node through encryption of the data at rest.

element.name: Raw data storage
element.documentation: Storage of source data without any change.

element.name: Prepared data storage
element.documentation: Storage of data that has been processed applies standard technical rules that are business-agnostic: type formats, management of null value, generation of unique keys, etc.

element.name: Information data storage
element.documentation: Storage of data that has been prepared for a specific business use-case: insights, features calculated by data science, aggregations. Includes the capability to execute low-latency queries for streaming jobs.

element.name: Data copy
element.documentation: Function that allows copying of datasets between different environments.

element.name: Archiving & compressing
element.documentation: Archiving and compression functions to manage the data lifecycle and optimize storage resources.

element.name: Comply with regulations (e.g., privacy, Solvency II …)
Store data as an asset including metadata
Reduce the total cost of ownership
Generate business value leveraging new data capabilities (e.g., data science ...)

node.label: Other Internal Capabilities
node.documentation: Other capabilities available within the organization.

node.label: External Capabilities
node.documentation: Capabilities provided by actors external to the organization.

An application function represents automated behavior that can be performed by an application component

A capability represents an ability that an active structure element, such as an organization, person, or system, possesses. Here we describe capabilities provided by the Information Technology (IT) department
A data object represents data structured for automated processing
A stakeholder is the role of an individual, team, or organization (or classes thereof) that represents their interests in the outcome of the architecture.
A goal represents a high-level statement of intent, direction, or desired end state for an organization and its stakeholders.
The influence relationship models that an element affects the implementation or achievement of some motivation element.
A capability represents an ability that an organization, person, or system possesses (TOGAF® Standard, Version 9.2)
Capabilities provided by the Information Technology (IT) department of the organization considered
External Digital Capabilities with which the organization has to interact
